Images have emerged of two plane tickets believed to have been purchased using stolen passports for the missing Malaysian Airlines flight.

As relatives of the 239 people on Malaysia Airlines flight MH370 continued to wait anxiously for news of their loved ones, attention has focused on how two passengers boarded the aircraft using stolen passports.

Pictures have now emerged of what appears to be the tickets purchased by the stolen passport users, as Malaysian police say one of them has been identified.

